label.value: regulation of vesicle fusion with Golgi apparatus

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of vesicle fusion with Golgi apparatus.

label.value: negative regulation of vesicle fusion with Golgi apparatus

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of vesicle fustion with Golgi apparatus.

label.value: positive regulation of vesicle fusion with Golgi apparatus

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of vesicle fusion with Golgi apparatus.

label.value: regulation of basement membrane organization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the assembly, disassembly or arrangement of constituent parts of the basement membrane.

label.value: regulation of actomyosin structure organization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures containing both actin and myosin or paramyosin.

label.value: cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cardiac muscle myoblasts, resulting in the expansion of a cardiac muscle myoblast cell population. A cardiac myoblast is a precursor cell that has been committed to a cardiac muscle cell fate but retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life.

label.value: regulation of cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation.

label.value: negative regulation of cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation.

label.value: positive regulation of cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation.

label.value: regulation of actin filament organization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of actin filament organization.

label.value: regulation of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation.

label.value: positive regulation of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation.

label.value: negative regulation of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation.

label.value: vesicle-mediated intercellular transport

value.value: A cellular transport process in which transported substances are moved in extracellular vesicles between cells; transported substances are enclosed in the vesicle lumen or located in the extracellular vesicle membrane.

label.value: positive regulation of animal organ morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of animal organ morphogenesis.

label.value: negative regulation of animal organ morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of animal organ morphogenesis.

label.value: regulation of compound eye photoreceptor cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of compound eye photoreceptor cell differentiation.

label.value: positive regulation of compound eye photoreceptor cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of compound eye photoreceptor cell differentiation.

label.value: negative regulation of compound eye photoreceptor cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of compound eye photoreceptor cell differentiation.

label.value: myotube cell migration

value.value: The orderly movement of a myotube cell from one site to another, often during the development of a multicellular organism. Myotubes are multinucleated cells that are formed when proliferating myoblasts exit the cell cycle, differentiate, and fuse.

label.value: regulation of myotube cell migration

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of myotube cell migration.

label.value: positive regulation of myotube cell migration

value.value: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of myotube cell migration.

label.value: negative regulation of myotube cell migration

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of myotube cell migration.

label.value: cellular anatomical entity

value.value: A part of a cellular organism that is either an immaterial entity or a material entity with granularity above the level of a protein complex but below that of an anatomical system. Or, a substance produced by a cellular organism with granularity above the level of a protein complex.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection

value.value: A prolongation or process extending from a cell and that is bounded by plasma membrane, e.g. a cilium, lamellipodium, or axon.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Formation of a prolongation or process extending and that is bounded by plasma membrane, e.g. a cilium, lamellipodium, or axon.

label.value: regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly.

label.value: negative regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly.

label.value: positive regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly.

label.value: regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection organization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of plasma membrane bounded cell projections.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection organization

value.value: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a plasma membrane bounded prolongation or process extending from a cell, e.g. a cilium or axon.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the anatomical structures of a plasma membrane bounded cell projection are generated and organized.

label.value: neuron projection cytoplasm

value.value: All of the contents of a plasma membrane bounded neuron projection, excluding the plasma membrane surrounding the projection.

label.value: steroid hormone biosynthetic process

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of any steroid hormone, naturally occurring substances secreted by specialized cells that affects the metabolism or behavior of other cells possessing functional receptors for the hormone.

label.value: negative regulation of protein localization to chromatin

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to chromatin.

label.value: positive regulation of protein localization to chromatin

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to chromatin.

label.value: regulation of blastocyst development

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of blastocyst development.

label.value: larynx morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the larynx is generated and organized. The larynx is a continuation of the pharynx that is involved in breathing, sound production, and protecting the trachea against food aspiration.

label.value: larynx development

value.value: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a larynx from an initial condition to its mature state. This process begins with the formation of the larynx and ends with the mature structure. A larynx is a continuation of the pharynx that is involved in breathing, sound production, and protecting the trachea against food aspiration.

label.value: protein localization to motile cilium

value.value: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within a motile cilium.

label.value: cerebral blood circulation

value.value: The flow of blood through the network of arteries and veins supplying the cerebrum, enabling the transport of nutrients to the tissues and the removal of waste products.

label.value: regulation of cerebral blood circulation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cerebral blood circulation.

label.value: positive regulation of cerebral blood circulation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cerebral blood circulation.

label.value: negative regulation of cerebral blood circulation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cerebral blood circulation.

label.value: regulation of pigmentation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the deposition or modulates the distribution of coloring matter in an organism.

label.value: endothelial tube formation

value.value: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of an endothelial tube.

label.value: meiotic nuclear division

value.value: One of the two nuclear divisions that occur as part of the meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: mitotic nuclear division

value.value: A mitotic cell cycle process comprising the steps by which the nucleus of a eukaryotic cell divides; the process involves condensation of chromosomal DNA into a highly compacted form. Canonically, mitosis produces two daughter nuclei whose chromosome complement is identical to that of the mother cell.

label.value: exocytic process

value.value: The cellular processes that contribute to exocytosis.

label.value: organelle localization by membrane tethering

value.value: The process by which an organelle membrane interacts with another membrane via molecular tethers that physically bridge the two membranes and attach them to each other.
